00:20:10.620 --> 00:20:15.540
These alien spirits are what keep humans
from fulfilling their full potential.

00:20:15.540 --> 00:20:19.340
Ian now experiences perhaps the most
violent dissonance in his life.

00:20:19.340 --> 00:20:22.100
If he rejects the alien story, he's out.

00:20:22.100 --> 00:20:26.280
And all the time, energy and money
he's invested in the group has been wasted.

00:20:26.280 --> 00:20:28.740
The group's strict policy of shunning dissenters

00:20:28.740 --> 00:20:33.280
also means the loss of his wife,
his children and all his friends.

00:20:33.290 --> 00:20:35.890
But beyond even these threatening realities

00:20:35.890 --> 00:20:39.180
is a deep-seated belief that will
keep him under the group's influence

00:20:39.180 --> 00:20:41.720
haemorrhaging money for another two years:

00:20:41.720 --> 00:20:43.680
'I could never be manipulated'.

00:20:43.680 --> 00:20:49.480
To him, the only folks who fall for cons
are gullible, acquiescent, stupid.

00:20:49.480 --> 00:20:51.580
And that's just not him.

00:20:51.580 --> 00:20:54.280
And indeed that wasn't him

00:20:54.280 --> 00:20:56.660
Nonetheless he was recruited.

00:20:56.660 --> 00:20:59.040
Not because of some personality deficiency.

00:20:59.040 --> 00:21:01.260
But simply because he's a human being

00:21:01.260 --> 00:21:06.300
who — like all of us — possesses a brain
that's evolved to strive towards consistency.

00:21:06.300 --> 00:21:08.380
In his extreme state of dissonance

00:21:08.380 --> 00:21:14.320
Ian is led directly into a counselling session
to nullify his emotional reaction.

00:21:18.580 --> 00:21:20.600
A few years ago, a woman wrote to me to tell me

00:21:20.600 --> 00:21:24.340
she'd once thought I used demonic
psychological techniques in my videos.

00:21:24.340 --> 00:21:27.640
She'd been in a very controlling
fundamentalist religious group at the time

00:21:27.640 --> 00:21:33.100
and was disturbed to find herself feeling persuaded by some of the atheist counter-arguments I was presenting.

00:21:33.100 --> 00:21:36.880
She was convinced I'd used satanic mind control
to put her under a spell.

00:21:36.880 --> 00:21:41.900
This was no random rationalisation. Her group had told her this was how the atheists got you.

00:21:41.900 --> 00:21:44.400
And she was terrified it had happened to her.

00:21:44.400 --> 00:21:45.800
To try and break the spell

00:21:45.800 --> 00:21:50.260
she watched the same videos over and over
to figure out exactly how I'd corrupted her.

00:21:50.260 --> 00:21:54.820
It was during this process of analysis that she
came to realise the simpler explanation:

00:21:54.820 --> 00:21:57.640
she'd been persuaded by legitimate counter-arguments.

00:21:57.640 --> 00:21:59.220
She then realised something else:

00:21:59.220 --> 00:22:00.600
she'd become an atheist.

00:22:00.600 --> 00:22:04.880
This woman's story is an illustration of how manipulative groups develop strategies

00:22:04.880 --> 00:22:07.680
to put critics in no-win situations.

00:22:07.680 --> 00:22:09.660
If I fail to persuade, I lose.

00:22:09.660 --> 00:22:13.720
If I succeed in persuading,
I must be cheating, therefore I lose.

00:22:13.720 --> 00:22:17.880
Manipulative groups often possess a
wealth of ready-made rationalisations

00:22:17.880 --> 00:22:22.540
deviously designed so that their members'
cognitive dissonance is resolved in the group's favour.

00:22:22.540 --> 00:22:26.180
Some of them involve splitting
a single concept into two categories.

00:22:26.180 --> 00:22:28.920
We saw this with our hypothetical
friend from evil group A

00:22:28.920 --> 00:22:32.680
whose goodness was invalidated by
repackaging it as a deception.

00:22:32.680 --> 00:22:35.600
Whatever good she did only proved her deceitfulness.

00:22:35.600 --> 00:22:40.040
Here, goodness was effectively split into
true goodness and false goodness.

00:22:40.040 --> 00:22:42.240
Group A's goodness was always false.

00:22:42.240 --> 00:22:45.620
The authors of the Bible perform
a similar split in regard to wisdom

00:22:45.620 --> 00:22:49.900
dividing it into true godly wisdom and
false worldly wisdom.

00:22:49.900 --> 00:22:53.960
Worldly wisdom, which employs
human philosophy reason and logic,

00:22:53.960 --> 00:22:55.880
is dismissed in various books

00:22:55.880 --> 00:22:57.940
including Proverbs and Romans.

00:22:57.940 --> 00:23:00.020
But 1 Corinthians goes further.

00:23:00.020 --> 00:23:04.380
In chapter 1, we're told that godly wisdom
appears foolish to the worldly wise;

00:23:04.380 --> 00:23:08.820
that Yahweh has deliberately chosen foolish means
by which to confound the worldly wise

00:23:08.820 --> 00:23:11.080
turning the worldly wise into fools.

00:23:11.080 --> 00:23:16.179
This repackaging of wisdom allows the group
to rebuff all criticisms out of hand.

00:23:16.179 --> 00:23:18.859
Of course the critics think their religion
is foolish!

00:23:18.860 --> 00:23:23.080
Their God deliberately made their beliefs
incomprehensible to the worldly wise!

00:23:23.080 --> 00:23:28.120
Manipulative groups sometimes try to shield themselves from their critics by keeping their beliefs secret.

00:23:28.120 --> 00:23:30.480
Some groups suggest their beliefs are so potent

00:23:30.480 --> 00:23:34.100
they could strike down or even kill the uninitiated.

00:23:34.100 --> 00:23:38.180
When he was recruited into the Unification Church,
otherwise known as the Moonies,

00:23:38.180 --> 00:23:42.740
Steven Hassan, a leading writer, speaker and
counsellor in the field of manipulative groups.

00:23:42.740 --> 00:23:46.360
was told: 'You wouldn't feed a baby
thick pieces of steak would you? ....

00:23:46.360 --> 00:23:49.660
.... You have to feed a baby something
it can digest, like formula ....

00:23:49.660 --> 00:23:54.160
.... Well these people are spiritual babies.
Don't tell them more than they can handle ....

00:23:54.160 --> 00:23:55.580
.... or they'll die.'

00:23:55.580 --> 00:24:00.220
Lafayette Ronald Hubbard, founder of
pseudoscientific dianetics and scientology

00:24:00.220 --> 00:24:04.180
suggested that if folks were told about
Scientology's Xenu (Xemu) creation myth

00:24:04.190 --> 00:24:07.850
without appropriate preparation,
they might develop pneumonia.

00:24:07.850 --> 00:24:13.300
The Xenu story has become pretty common knowledge due to countless testimonies from ex-scientologists.

00:24:13.300 --> 00:24:18.140
But a global Xenu-induced pneumonia
epidemic has yet to be reported.

00:24:18.140 --> 00:24:20.520
Some groups claim it's pointless
to try and explain beliefs

00:24:20.520 --> 00:24:23.440
that are too advanced for non-members to comprehend.

00:24:23.440 --> 00:24:26.120
Heaven's Gate was a UFO religious group

00:24:26.120 --> 00:24:30.400
who committed mass suicide by ingesting
phenobarbital mixed into apple sauce

00:24:30.400 --> 00:24:33.420
believing this would allow their souls
to be picked up on a spacecraft

00:24:33.420 --> 00:24:35.300
trailing the Hale-Bopp comet.

00:24:35.300 --> 00:24:38.340
In a testimony video recorded shortly before their deaths

00:24:38.340 --> 00:24:42.460
one member used the analogy of a person
on a doctoral degree in quantum mechanics

00:24:42.460 --> 00:24:45.700
trying to explain to a second grader what he's learned.

00:24:45.700 --> 00:24:49.480
Another favourite manoeuvre used
by manipulative groups to deflect criticism

00:24:49.480 --> 00:24:52.300
is to develop a persecution narrative.

00:24:52.300 --> 00:24:58.480
Here, rather than splitting a single concept into two,
the group will instead join distinct concepts into one.

00:24:58.480 --> 00:25:02.900
Persecution is about the systemic
mistreatment of an individual or group.

00:25:02.900 --> 00:25:05.660
It's about cruel and unfair behaviour.

00:25:05.660 --> 00:25:11.420
Where a group is angrily criticised and condemned
for social legal and/or ethical violations

00:25:11.420 --> 00:25:14.020
that's not persecution. That's protest.

00:25:14.020 --> 00:25:19.140
Government officials jailed for criminally denying
the rights of people they personally deem unworthy

00:25:19.140 --> 00:25:22.160
are not being persecuted for their religious beliefs.

00:25:22.160 --> 00:25:26.900
Parents jailed for letting children die
by denying them vital medical assistance.

00:25:26.900 --> 00:25:30.060
are not being persecuted for their religious beliefs.

00:25:30.060 --> 00:25:34.740
They're being punished for their own cruel and
unfair behaviour towards their fellow humans.

00:25:34.740 --> 00:25:38.760
By repackaging appropriate protest
and punishment as persecution

00:25:38.760 --> 00:25:43.040
not only do manipulative groups
get to commit all kinds of abuses guilt-free.

00:25:43.040 --> 00:25:45.940
they get to feel like martyrs while they're doing it.

00:25:45.940 --> 00:25:49.180
Consoling them further are passages
from their holy books

00:25:49.180 --> 00:25:51.520
that promise great rewards for being persecuted

00:25:51.520 --> 00:25:53.280
— after they die of course.

00:25:53.280 --> 00:25:55.180
It's been put to me more than once

00:25:55.180 --> 00:25:59.480
that critics don't stand a chance against
belief systems that are so psychologically ring-fenced

00:25:59.480 --> 00:26:02.360
and can wield such gargantuan carrots and sticks.

00:26:02.360 --> 00:26:04.700
And yet critics to get through.

00:26:04.700 --> 00:26:06.840
Though the odds are stacked in the group's favour

00:26:06.840 --> 00:26:09.740
dissonance isn't guaranteed to go their way.

00:26:09.740 --> 00:26:12.840
Time after time, something sticks.

00:26:12.840 --> 00:26:13.900
A phrase.

00:26:13.900 --> 00:26:14.980
An image.

00:26:14.980 --> 00:26:16.060
An argument.

00:26:16.060 --> 00:26:17.260
A question.

00:26:17.260 --> 00:26:23.800
That tiny fragment of clarity is sometimes all it takes
to instigate a process of self-extraction.

00:26:23.800 --> 00:26:27.960
So critics take heart — and speak out.

00:26:33.470 --> 00:26:38.810
Our minds are vast networks of ideas,
striving not necessarily for truth

00:26:38.810 --> 00:26:40.960
but for internal consistency

00:26:40.970 --> 00:26:45.040
so that that the injection of a false idea into
that network can have a domino effect

00:26:45.040 --> 00:26:47.120
distorting the ideas around it.

00:26:47.120 --> 00:26:49.740
From this, three things become clear.

00:26:49.740 --> 00:26:56.060
One, the importance of anchoring our beliefs
in firm evidence and valid, sound logic.

00:26:56.060 --> 00:27:00.260
The more we lower these standards,
the easier false ideas slip inside.

00:27:00.260 --> 00:27:03.700
Two, the importance of getting
comfortable with not knowing.

00:27:03.700 --> 00:27:06.400
If we don't know whether an assertion is true or false

00:27:06.400 --> 00:27:08.060
we need to be real about that.

00:27:08.060 --> 00:27:10.360
Taking the dishonest position of 'I know'

00:27:10.360 --> 00:27:11.800
based on what we want to believe

00:27:11.800 --> 00:27:15.960
could lead to false rationalisations
if future evidence contradicts us.

00:27:15.960 --> 00:27:18.240
Taking be honest position of 'I don't know'

00:27:18.240 --> 00:27:20.860
mean future evidence can be assessed openly

00:27:20.860 --> 00:27:24.840
Three, the importance of understanding
the techniques of manipulative groups.

00:27:24.840 --> 00:27:29.880
These groups are practiced at insinuating
false ideas into our cognitive networks

00:27:29.880 --> 00:27:32.100
gradually turning our worlds upside down

00:27:32.100 --> 00:27:34.740
so that while we think we're still grounded in reality

00:27:34.740 --> 00:27:37.360
we've instead hooked ourselves to clouds.

00:27:37.360 --> 00:27:39.360
and we're drifting slowly away

00:27:39.360 --> 00:27:41.560
from all sense and reason.

00:27:43.980 --> 00:27:46.800
One of the best preventative
measures against recruitment?

00:27:46.800 --> 00:27:48.800
Learn about recruitment techniques.

00:27:48.800 --> 00:27:50.780
One of the best ways of doing that?

00:27:50.780 --> 00:27:53.260
Listen to the stories of the people who've been there.

00:27:53.260 --> 00:27:56.540
Manipulative groups are often made
of folks just like you and me.

00:27:56.540 --> 00:28:01.320
That's what makes them so effective —
because the folks who recruit us are just like us.

00:28:01.320 --> 00:28:06.620
Another preventive measure is to disarm the beliefs
that can be used against us to induce dissonance.

00:28:06.620 --> 00:28:08.300
As Aronson and Mills showed

00:28:08.300 --> 00:28:12.400
we're sometimes fooled into thinking that groups
who get us to jump through hoops are worthwhile

00:28:12.400 --> 00:28:15.080
because we want to believe our time isn't wasted.

00:28:15.080 --> 00:28:19.600
That phrase 'want to believe' is like
a signpost, saying: 'Examine me!'

00:28:19.600 --> 00:28:24.580
Is this belief justified or is it a wishful distortion?

00:28:24.580 --> 00:28:28.620
The fact is our time is sometimes
wasted by undeserving pursuits.

00:28:28.620 --> 00:28:32.200
When we acknowledge that,
this particular manipulation is disarmed.

00:28:32.200 --> 00:28:35.840
And we can apply the same principle
to many other ideas we want to believe

00:28:35.840 --> 00:28:37.420
that can be used against us.

00:28:37.420 --> 00:28:42.540
For instance, that we're always right
or that we can always judge a person's character.

00:28:42.540 --> 00:28:45.140
I'm sure you can think of other examples.

00:28:45.140 --> 00:28:48.940
I'll end on one: wanting to believe
we can't be manipulated.

00:28:48.940 --> 00:28:51.460
Of course we're manipulated all the time.

00:28:51.469 --> 00:28:53.949
Manipulated by adverts to buy products.

00:28:53.949 --> 00:28:56.729
Manipulated by loved ones to do favours.

00:28:56.729 --> 00:29:00.449
But if we ever have the misfortune
of getting recruited by a manipulative group

00:29:00.449 --> 00:29:06.020
this wishful distortion could block all our escape routes,
keeping us in a state of denial.

00:29:06.020 --> 00:29:09.660
Seems paradoxical, but the moment
we admit we can be manipulated

00:29:09.660 --> 00:29:12.180
We instantly reduce our chances of being manipulated

00:29:12.180 --> 00:29:15.200
because we become more open
to evidence that we have been.

00:29:15.200 --> 00:29:19.460
Chances are some folks watching this
are in a manipulative group right now

00:29:19.460 --> 00:29:22.919
excusing their group's abuses and hypocrisies.

00:29:22.919 --> 00:29:27.859
The more aware we are of their methods
and of our own human quirks and biases

00:29:27.860 --> 00:29:32.260
the less successful they'll be in
keeping us doing what keeps them alive:

00:29:32.260 --> 00:29:33.900
bending truth.

